DESCRIPTION:Overview:\nMacros: 3550 kcal\, 165 g protein\, 520 g carbs\, 1
 00 g fat\nCategory: sprint\nRun volume: 3 km\nAdjustments:\n- Adjusted fo
 r schedule constraints.\n\nWarm-Up:\n- 10 min easy plus skips\, ankling\,
  hip openers\, and 3 relaxed strides.\n\nMain Work:\n- Progression: add p
 ower volume only when jumps stay crisp and knees stay quiet the next day.
  Reduce volume by 25-40% before adding intensity.\n- Plyometrics: pogos 3
  x 20 sec\, low broad jumps 4 x 2\, and med-ball slams 4 x 5 if available
 .\n- Hill sprint technique: 4-6 x 8-10 sec at fast but controlled effort.
 \n- Functional work: sled push if easy to set up or farmer carries 4 x 30
  m.\n- Core: crawling 3 x 20 m or dead bug 3 x 8 per side.\n\nRun:\n- Pla
 nned running volume: 3 km.\n\nFueling:\n- Hit daily macros\, keep protein
  near target\, and place carbohydrates before and after training.\n\nReco
 very:\n- Sleep window stays 22:00-06:00\; add mobility if joints feel sti
 ff.
